The paper discusses the use of neural networks for approximating and replacing code regions within HPC applications to improve performance, which falls under the category of neural networks (cs.NE). Additionally, the paper also discusses the potential for reducing latencies and improving accuracy, which could be relevant to the categories of human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC). The paper also mentions the use of simulations and modeling complicated relationships, which could be relevant to the categories of software engineering (cs.SE) and machine learning (cs.LG).
